  <p>
    We can now see that <m>y(x)=\frac{2+2x^2+2x^4}{1+x^4}</m> has a
    <term>horizontal asymptote</term> at <m>y=2</m>. If you haven<rsq/>t
    already done so consider graphing this function to confirm.
  </p>


