</p>
<p>
 Of these, only the
last two are L<rsq/>HÃ´pital  Indeterminate forms. The others must be evaluated
by some method other than directly applying L<rsq/>HÃ´pital<rsq/>s Rule. Often this
simply means algebraically rearranging them into a L<rsq/>HÃ´pital
Indeterminate.
</p>
